  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior / Procurement Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p><p><strong>Procurement & Supplier Management</strong></p><ul><li>Identify, evaluate and qualify suppliers for parts (off-the-shelf, fabricated, and electrical/ electronic) and services</li><li>Monitor supplier performance metrics and implement corrective actions and continuous improvement plans</li><li>Place and manage purchase orders</li><li>Maintain accurate and timely procurement data in ERP system</li><li>Ensure procurement activities adhere to internal\npolicies and controls</li></ul><p><strong>Strategic Supply Chain Management</strong></p><ul><li>Drive supply chain initiatives, such as cost reduction, multi-sourcing, and inventory planning</li><li>Continually analyze market trends and supply risks; develop mitigation strategies accordingly</li></ul><p><u><strong>Qualifications</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Engineering (Mechanical, Electrical/ Electronics, Mechatronics, Industrial, Materials)</li><li>2+ years of relevant experience in procurement or sourcing, preferably within semiconductor equipment, precision manufacturing or high-tech industries</li><li>Ability to interpret technical drawings and specifications</li><li>Proficiency in ERP systems and Microsoft Excel</li></ul><p><u><strong>About Aurigin</strong></u></p><p>Founded in 2001, Aurigin designs, develops and delivers smart automation equipment and solutions to semiconductor and electrical manufacturing customers.  Our systems, such as our flagship BGA ball mount equipment, are installed globally and help produce complex semiconductor devices that power everything from our daily lives to the next frontier of intelligence.</p>",
